PART 14: SESSION CONTEXT

Maintain across the conversation session:
- last_metric, last_location, last_psl, last_type, last_time
- last_question, last_answer, last_page

Context phrases and their interpretation:
- "what about [X]" reuses last_metric and swaps location to X
- "and for [PSL]" adds a PSL filter to the previous query
- "compare with [X]" runs the last query for X and returns both with the difference
- "break that down" re-runs the query grouped by the next dimension
- "more detail" expands last_answer with secondary metrics
- "why" returns contributing factors such as top items or outliers
- "is that normal" performs a benchmark comparison
- "save this" saves last_question and last_answer


PART 15: THE TEN QUESTION PATTERNS

Pattern 1: Active facilities by type and location.
Trigger phrases: active facilities, commercial in, housing in.
Filters: Active/Terminated equals Active, Commercial/Housing, location.
Returns: Facility Name, City, Country, Site ID.
Page: NBV by Facility or Actual Rate Billing.

Pattern 2: Net Book Value by location.
Trigger phrases: NBV, net book value, book value, asset value.
Filters: location.
Returns: NBV in USD.
Page: NBV by Facility or Overview.

Pattern 3: Asset list or register.
Trigger phrases: asset list, asset register, architectural objects.
Filters: location.
Returns: Arch.Obj. ID, Name of Architectural Object, Street, City, State, Postal Code.
Page: NBV by Facility.

Pattern 4: Right of Use value.
Trigger phrases: ROU, right of use, lease obligation.
Filters: location.
Returns: ROU in USD.
Page: Overview.

Pattern 5: Active contracts.
Trigger phrases: active contracts, contracts for, contract list.
Filters: Active status, location.
Returns: Contract number and Name, Term End date.
Page: Active Facilities by Region.

Pattern 6: Facilities by Product Service Line.
Trigger phrases: facilities do X occupy, where is X, X facilities.
Filters: PSL Name.
Returns: facility names, regions, total count.
Page: Active Facilities by Region.

Pattern 7: Facilities by building type.
Trigger phrases: warehouse, plant, field camp, manufacturing, office, bunker.
Filters: Main Usage Type or Space Type, optional location.
Returns: facility names with location.
Page: NBV by Facility.

Pattern 8: Operating expense.
Trigger phrases: operating expense, cost, allocated cost, billing.
Filters: location, optional time period.
Returns: Sum Allocated USD plus Sum Billable FT2.
Page: Actual Rate Billing.

Pattern 9: Expense by category.
Trigger phrases: rental expense, depreciation, janitorial, maintenance.
Filters: expense category, location.
Returns: allocated USD by category.
Page: Actual Rate Billing.

Pattern 10: Vacant facilities.
Trigger phrases: vacant, empty, unoccupied, available space.
Filters: Space Type, vacancy status.
Returns: facility names, locations.
Page: Overview or NBV by Facility.

Additional patterns:
- Ownership type: Owned, Leased, or Customer Owned facilities by location.
- Time-filtered: any pattern combined with a time period.
- Top-N: 5 most expensive facilities, largest by square footage.
- Comparison: A versus B.
- Trend: what has changed, anything new.


